node.text:
Follow 👉  @bodysmartfitness for the best mindset, nutrition and fitness tips 👉  Follow @bodysmartfitness 
 
❤️If you do not address what is going on deep in your head and heart you'll never get to where you want to go. 
 
👉 Jaymie co - founder at body smart explained "When Body Smart first started four and half years ago we pushed hard on the fitness and diet side of things. As the business grew we wanted to also grow as people so we started hiring business coaches.⁣" 
 
🧠 "We've invested an insane amount of money over the last few years on improving the business, over this time one thing that stood out was how our personal mindset shifted when working with the different coaches. 
 
💪 "Within months of being coached ourselves we knew that we had to adopt more mindset work into our coaching. We delved deep and studied all we could on different methods and explored the theory of psychology and neuroscience.⁣ " 
 
🙌 "It was without a doubt the best thing we had done. We are better coaches as well as better people.⁣" 
 
❤ "Dealing with the stuff on the inside and how you feel in your heart and head can be a rocky process. It can also be fascinating and enlightening but it isn't a process that you should try to unpick alone." 
 
🧠"That's why we focus on mindset more so than anything else with clients. We see things from a different perspective, find answers and help you emerge with true self-awareness, self-acceptance and self-love.⁣" 
 
🔍"Finding self-love within yourself is the hardest part of the process but the most rewarding.⁣" 
 
💬 Find out more on how @bodysmartfitness can help you on your journey by messaging them directly with #LETSGO
